article.headline: Marist 71, Manhattan 62
article.story: POUGHKEEPESIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Will Wittington scored 19 points to lead Marist to a 71-62 win over Manhattan in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference on Sunday. Ryan Stilphen had 12 points and 10 rebounds, Will McClurkin had 11 points and 11 rebounds, and Jared Jordan scored 14 points for Marist (6-7, 3-1 MAAC). Peter Mulligan led Manhattan (6-5, 1-2) with 14 points. Mike Konovelchick scored 13 and C.J. Anderson added 12 points and nine rebounds for the Jaspers. Manhattan led 28-26 at halftime, but Marist opened the second half with a 13-3 run over 4:11 to take a 39-33 lead with 14:48 remaining. The Jaspers came back with a 12-3 run to pull within one basket, 64-62, on a tip-in by Konovelchick with a minute to go, but could get no closer. Whittington hit 7-of-8 free throws in the game's last 57 seconds to solidify the Marist victory.
